## The Contract

This repository uses **Build.MD** — a repo-native project management system. All specs,
stories, decisions, and progress tracking live in Git as structured Markdown. There is no
external tracker. The repo is the single source of truth.

### What This Means for You (Agent or Human)

1. **Before writing code**, check if there's a relevant spec in `docs/specs/` or story in `docs/stories/`
2. **When committing**, include `Story: STORY-NNN` or `Spec: SPEC-XXX` trailers on feat/fix commits
3. **Keep notes** in `docs/notes/{your-name}/` — daily append-only journals of what you worked on and why
4. **Before merging a PR**, distill your raw notes into a cleaned summary or ADR in `docs/decisions/`
5. **Never hand-edit** `.ledger/changes.json` — it's machine-generated from your commits

### Directory Map

```
docs/
  specs/           ← Requirement specifications (YAML frontmatter + Markdown body)
  stories/         ← User stories with acceptance criteria
    archive/       ← Completed stories (never deleted)
  notes/
    {contributor}/ ← Your daily working notes
    agents/        ← AI agent session notes
  decisions/       ← Architecture Decision Records
  reports/         ← Generated change reports
.ledger/
  changes.json     ← Append-only change ledger
```

