### Frontmatter Schema

Every spec file (`docs/specs/*.md`) must start with:

```yaml
---
id: SPEC-{domain}-{number}
title: "Human-readable title"
status: proposed | active | implemented | deprecated
owner: contributor-name
stories: [STORY-NNN, ...]
paths: ["src/relevant/**"]
acceptance:
  - "Criterion 1"
  - "Criterion 2"
updated_at: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

Every story file (`docs/stories/*.md`) must start with:

```yaml
---
id: STORY-{number}
title: "Human-readable title"
status: {{STATUS_VALUES}}
spec: SPEC-{domain}-{number}
owner: contributor-name
priority: critical | high | medium | low
blocked_by: []
acceptance:
  - "Criterion 1"
updated_at: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

### Commit Convention

Use Conventional Commits with trailers:

```
type(scope): description

Optional body explaining why, not what.

Story: STORY-NNN
Spec: SPEC-XXX-NNN
```

**Types:** feat, fix, perf, refactor, docs, test, chore, style, ci

**Enforcement level: {{ENFORCEMENT_LEVEL}}**

{{ENFORCEMENT_RULES}}

### Note-Taking Contract

When you work on something, write what you did and why in your notes file:

```
docs/notes/{your-name}/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md
```

For AI agents, use:
```
docs/notes/agents/{agent-type}-{session-id}/{YYYY-MM-DD}.md
```

Raw notes are informal — bullet points, stream of consciousness, debug logs, whatever
helps capture context. Before a PR merges, the important findings should be distilled
into a cleaned note or ADR in `docs/decisions/`.

### Creating New Artifacts

**New spec:**
```bash
# Copy the template
cp meta/schemas/spec-template.md docs/specs/SPEC-{domain}-{number}.md
# Fill in the frontmatter and body
```

**New story:**
```bash
cp meta/schemas/story-template.md docs/stories/STORY-{number}.md
```

**New decision:**
```bash
cp meta/schemas/adr-template.md docs/decisions/{number}-{slug}.md
```

### Locking (Multi-Agent/Multi-User)

If you need exclusive access to a story or spec, add to its frontmatter:

```yaml
locked_by: "your-name-or-agent:session-id"
locked_at: "ISO-8601 timestamp"
```

Locks expire after 30 minutes. To force-unlock, add `Force-Unlock: STORY-NNN` as a
commit trailer and explain why in the commit body.

### Local Dashboard

To visualize progress:

```bash
python scripts/serve.py
# Opens http://localhost:3456 with the Kanban board and change timeline
```

The dashboard reads from Git + frontmatter. It has no data of its own.

